ilog.cplex

Enum IloCplex.Callback.Context.Info

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<IloCplex.Callback.Context.Info>
      • ilog.cplex.IloCplex.Callback.Context.Info
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<IloCplex.Callback.Context.Info>
    Enclosing class:
    IloCplex.Callback.Context

    public static enum IloCplex.Callback.Context.Info
extends java.lang.Enum<IloCplex.Callback.Context.Info>
    Constants to query information from a CPLEX callback. This enumeration defines the various pieces of information that can be queried from IloCplex.Callback.Context.getIntInfo(Info), IloCplex.Callback.Context.getLongInfo(Info), IloCplex.Callback.Context.getDoubleInfo(Info). Refer to Callback context in the Reference Manual of the Callable Library (C API) for further details about these values.
